ieee8021STMib.name: ieee8021STMib

revisions.description: Published as part of IEEE Std 802.1Q 2017 revision. Cross references updated and corrected.
Revised to include Set-And-Hold-MAC and Set-And-Release-MAC in the description of ieee8021STAdminControlList and ieee8021STOperControlList. Published as part of IEEE Std 802.1Qbu.
Initial version published as part of IEEE Std 802.1Qbv.

ieee8021STMib.description: The Bridge MIB module for managing devices that support the Scheduled Traffic Enhancements for IEEE 802.1Q Bridges. Unless otherwise indicated, the references in this MIB module are to IEEE Std 802.1Q. Copyright (C) IEEE (2018). This version of this MIB module is part of IEEE Std 802.1Q; see the draft itself for full legal notices.

IEEE8021STTrafficClassValue.name: IEEE8021STTrafficClassValue
IEEE8021STTrafficClassValue.description: A traffic class value. This is the numerical value associated with a traffic class in a Bridge. Larger values are associated with higher priority traffic classes.

IEEE8021STPTPtimeValue.name: IEEE8021STPTPtimeValue
IEEE8021STPTPtimeValue.description: A PTPtime value, represented as a 48-bit unsigned integer number of seconds and a 32-bit unsigned integer number of nanoseconds. The first 6 octets represent the number of seconds: the first octet is the most significant octet of the 48-bit seconds value and the sixth octet is the least significant octet of the seconds value. The remaining octets, 7 through 10, represent the number of nanoseconds: the seventh octet is the most significant octet of the 32-bit nanoseconds value and the tenth octet is the least significant octet of the nanoseconds value.

ieee8021STMaxSDUTable.name: ieee8021STMaxSDUTable
ieee8021STMaxSDUTable.description: A table containing a set of max SDU parameters, one for each traffic class. All writeable objects in this table must be persistent over power up restart/reboot.

ieee8021STMaxSDUEntry.name: ieee8021STMaxSDUEntry
ieee8021STMaxSDUEntry.description: A list of objects containing Max SDU size for each traffic class supported by the Port.

ieee8021STTrafficClass.name: ieee8021STTrafficClass
ieee8021STTrafficClass.description: The traffic class number associated with the row of the table. A row in this table is created for each traffic class that is supported by the Port

ieee8021STMaxSDU.name: ieee8021STMaxSDU
ieee8021STMaxSDU.description: The value of the MaxSDU parameter for the traffic class. This value is represented as an unsigned integer. A value of 0 is interpreted as the max SDU size supported by the underlying MAC. The default value of the MaxSDU parameter is 0. The value of this object MUST be retained across reinitializations of the management system.

ieee8021TransmissionOverrun.name: ieee8021TransmissionOverrun
ieee8021TransmissionOverrun.description: A counter of transmission overrun events, where a PDU is still being transmitted by a MAC at the time when the transmission gate for the queue closed.

ieee8021STParametersTable.name: ieee8021STParametersTable
ieee8021STParametersTable.description: A table that contains the per-port manageable parameters for traffic scheduling. For a given Port, a row in the table exists. All writable objects in this table must be persistent over power up restart/reboot.

ieee8021STParametersEntry.name: ieee8021STParametersEntry
ieee8021STParametersEntry.description: A list of objects that contains the manageable parameters for traffic scheduling for a port.

ieee8021STGateEnabled.name: ieee8021STGateEnabled
ieee8021STGateEnabled.description: The GateEnabled parameter determines whether traffic scheduling is active (true) or inactive (false). The value of this object MUST be retained across reinitializations of the management system.

ieee8021STAdminGateStates.name: ieee8021STAdminGateStates
ieee8021STAdminGateStates.description: The administrative value of the GateStates parameter for the Port. The bits of the octet represent the gate states for the corresponding traffic classes; the MS bit corresponds to traffic class 7, the LS bit to traffic class 0. A bit value of 0 indicates closed; a bit value of 1 indicates open. The value of this object MUST be retained across reinitializations of the management system.

ieee8021STOperGateStates.name: ieee8021STOperGateStates
ieee8021STOperGateStates.description: The operational value of the GateStates parameter for the Port. The bits of the octet represent the gate states for the corresponding traffic classes; the MS bit corresponds to traffic class 7, the LS bit to traffic class 0. A bit value of 0 indicates closed; a bit value of 1 indicates open.

ieee8021STAdminControlListLength.name: ieee8021STAdminControlListLength
ieee8021STAdminControlListLength.description: The administrative value of the ListMax parameter for the Port. The integer value indicates the number of entries (TLVs) in the AdminControlList. The value of this object MUST be retained across reinitializations of the management system.

ieee8021STOperControlListLength.name: ieee8021STOperControlListLength
ieee8021STOperControlListLength.description: The operational value of the ListMax parameter for the Port. The integer value indicates the number of entries (TLVs) in the OperControlList.

ieee8021STAdminControlList.name: ieee8021STAdminControlList
ieee8021STAdminControlList.description: The administrative value of the ControlList parameter for the Port. The octet string value represents the contents of the control list as an ordered list of entries, each encoded as a TLV, as follows. The first octet of each TLV is interpreted as an unsigned integer representing a gate operation name: 0: SetGateStates 1: Set-And-Hold-MAC 2: Set-And-Release-MAC 3-255: Reserved for future gate operations The second octet of the TLV is the length field, interpreted as an unsigned integer, indicating the number of octets of the value that follows the length. A length of zero indicates that there is no value (i.e., the gate operation has no parameters). The third through (3 + length -1)th octets encode the parameters of the gate operation, in the order that they appear in the definition of the operation in Table 8-6. Two parameter types are currently defined: - GateState: A GateState parameter is encoded in a single octet. The bits of the octet represent the gate states for the corresponding traffic classes; the MS bit corresponds to traffic class 7, the LS bit to traffic class 0. A bit value of 0 indicates closed; a bit value of 1 indicates open. - TimeInterval: A TimeInterval is encoded in 4 octets as a 32-bit unsigned integer, representing a number of nanoseconds. The first octet encodes the most significant 8 bits of the integer, and the fourth octet encodes the least significant 8 bits. The value of this object MUST be retained across reinitializations of the management system.

ieee8021STOperControlList.name: ieee8021STOperControlList
ieee8021STOperControlList.description: The operational value of the ListMax parameter for the Port. The octet string value represents the contents of the control list as an ordered list of TLVs, as follows. The first octet of each TLV is interpreted as a gate operation name: 0: SetGateStates 1: Set-And-Hold-MAC 2: Set-And-Release-MAC 3-255: Reserved for future gate operations The second octet of the TLV is the length field, interpreted as an unsigned integer, indicating the number of octets of the value that follows the length. A length of zero indicates that there is no value (i.e., the gate operation has no parameters). The third through (3 + length -1)th octets encode the parameters of the gate operation, in the order that they appear in the definition of the operation in Table 8-6. Two parameter types are currently defined: - GateState: A GateState parameter is encoded in a single octet. The bits of the octet represent the gate states for the corresponding traffic classes; the MS bit corresponds to traffic class 7, the LS bit to traffic class 0. A bit value of 0 indicates closed; a bit value of 1 indicates open. - TimeInterval: A TimeInterval is encoded in 4 octets as a 32-bit unsigned integer, representing a number of nanoseconds. The first octet encodes the most significant 8 bits of the integer, and the fourth octet encodes the least significant 8 bits.

ieee8021STAdminCycleTimeNumerator.name: ieee8021STAdminCycleTimeNumerator
ieee8021STAdminCycleTimeNumerator.description: The administrative value of the numerator of the CycleTime parameter for the Port. The numerator and denominator together represent the cycle time as a rational number of seconds. The value of this object MUST be retained across reinitializations of the management system.

ieee8021STAdminCycleTimeDenominator.name: ieee8021STAdminCycleTimeDenominator
ieee8021STAdminCycleTimeDenominator.description: The administrative value of the denominator of the CycleTime parameter for the Port. The numerator and denominator together represent the cycle time as a rational number of seconds. The value of this object MUST be retained across reinitializations of the management system.

ieee8021STOperCycleTimeNumerator.name: ieee8021STOperCycleTimeNumerator
ieee8021STOperCycleTimeNumerator.description: The operational value of the numerator of the CycleTime parameter for the Port. The numerator and denominator together represent the cycle time as a rational number of seconds.

ieee8021STOperCycleTimeDenominator.name: ieee8021STOperCycleTimeDenominator
ieee8021STOperCycleTimeDenominator.description: The operational value of the denominator of the CycleTime parameter for the Port. The numerator and denominator together represent the cycle time as a rational number of seconds.

ieee8021STAdminCycleTimeExtension.name: ieee8021STAdminCycleTimeExtension
ieee8021STAdminCycleTimeExtension.description: The administrative value of the CycleTimeExtension parameter for the Port. The value is an unsigned integer number of nanoseconds. The value of this object MUST be retained across reinitializations of the management system.

ieee8021STOperCycleTimeExtension.name: ieee8021STOperCycleTimeExtension
ieee8021STOperCycleTimeExtension.description: The operational value of the CycleTimeExtension parameter for the Port. The value is an unsigned integer number of nanoseconds.

ieee8021STAdminBaseTime.name: ieee8021STAdminBaseTime
ieee8021STAdminBaseTime.description: The administrative value of the BaseTime parameter for the Port. The value is a representation of a PTPtime value, consisting of a 48-bit integer number of seconds and a 32-bit integer number of nanoseconds. The value of this object MUST be retained across reinitializations of the management system.

ieee8021STOperBaseTime.name: ieee8021STOperBaseTime
ieee8021STOperBaseTime.description: The operationsl value of the BaseTime parameter for the Port. The value is a representation of a PTPtime value, consisting of a 48-bit integer number of seconds and a 32-bit integer number of nanoseconds.

ieee8021STConfigChange.name: ieee8021STConfigChange
ieee8021STConfigChange.description: The ConfigChange parameter signals the start of a configuration change when it is set to TRUE. This should only be done when the various administrative parameters are all set to appropriate values.

ieee8021STConfigChangeTime.name: ieee8021STConfigChangeTime
ieee8021STConfigChangeTime.description: The PTPtime at which the next config change is scheduled to occur. The value is a representation of a PTPtime value, consisting of a 48-bit integer number of seconds and a 32-bit integer number of nanoseconds. The value of this object MUST be retained across reinitializations of the management system.

ieee8021STTickGranularity.name: ieee8021STTickGranularity
ieee8021STTickGranularity.description: The granularity of the cycle time clock, represented as an unsigned number of tenths of nanoseconds. The value of this object MUST be retained across reinitializations of the management system.

ieee8021STCurrentTime.name: ieee8021STCurrentTime
ieee8021STCurrentTime.description: The current time, in PTPtime, as maintained by the local system. The value is a representation of a PTPtime value, consisting of a 48-bit integer number of seconds and a 32-bit integer number of nanoseconds.

ieee8021STConfigPending.name: ieee8021STConfigPending
ieee8021STConfigPending.description: The value of the ConfigPending state machine variable. The value is TRUE if a configuration change is in progress but has not yet completed.

ieee8021STConfigChangeError.name: ieee8021STConfigChangeError
ieee8021STConfigChangeError.description: A counter of the number of times that a re-configuration of the traffic schedule has been requested with the old schedule still running and the requested base time was in the past.

ieee8021STSupportedListMax.name: ieee8021STSupportedListMax
ieee8021STSupportedListMax.description: The maximum value supported by this Port of the AdminControlListLength and OperControlListLength parameters.

ieee8021STObjectsGroup.name: ieee8021STObjectsGroup
ieee8021STObjectsGroup.description: Objects that allow management of scheduled traffic.

ieee8021STCompliance.name: ieee8021STCompliance
ieee8021STCompliance.description: The compliance statement for devices supporting scheduled traffic. Support of the objects defined in this MIB module also requires support of the IEEE8021-BRIDGE-MIB; the provisions of 17.3.2 apply to implementations claiming support of this MIB.
